      "name": "Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Follow up with leads with PostgreSQL and Slack hands-free\n\n**Pattern:** Drip Sequence · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nFollow up with leads with PostgreSQL and Slack hands-free. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual outreach is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nHourly Schedule → Read Pending Queue (PostgreSQL) → Stamp & Shape Lead → Payload Valid? → Work in Batches → Aggregate Batch Results → Mark Completed in Google Sheets → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to drip sequence without manual effort\n- Anyone automating outreach in sales\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n- Scales without extra headcount\n- Improves response time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; Postgres connection; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "21eff46b-977f-0ff6-75b3-0dde2e023dbf",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "0834b943-63bc-0bca-7efe-554bd4e7e1be",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## ⏱ Rate limiting\n\nWork is batched and spaced with Wait so provider quotas aren't tripped. If you hit 429s, lower the batch size or raise the wait — throughput drops, reliability rises.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "576696d9-5a2e-d353-e80c-af8d0a138c34",
      "name": "⏱ Rate limiting"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your outreach process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 4
      },
